\cf0 **Page Name: must correspond to the heading of the CMS page (which appears in the table of contents). You must separate heading names with a ":". For example: heading1:heading2.\
**URL: The URL must correspond to the RSS feed.  The plugin will attempt to find feeds from the given URL in the standard fashion.  For further details, see the SimplePie documentation.\
\
Other Configuration\
-------------------\
Each item of the RSS feed will be displayed according to the rss.tpl file.  By default, this file shows the title of the post, a brief excerpt, and the source (URL/Title).  Users wishing to show each item differently can edit this file.  Two variables are loaded into this template: $feed and $item.  $feed is a SimplePie Feed object and $item is a SimplePie Item object.  For further description of the methods available on these objects, please consult the SimplePie documentation (http://www.simplepie.org).\
\
Known Limitations\
-----------------\
- Feed URL's are not validated on the settings page\
- Page Names are not checked against the CMS to make sure they exist\
- There is no feedback when feeds are not recognized properly or when there is any type of error.  The Page will likely just appear blank.\
